  [1] Or at least it uses power from renewable sources that could otherwise=
 power other activities, so that those other activities need to use carbon-=
emitting forms of power. Oh no of course *your* Bitcoin operation is totall=
y green, please email me about it.


  [2] This oversimplifies a bit: Some =E2=80=9Cplatform=E2=80=9D is operati=
onal stuff for portfolio companies (helping them with hiring and marketing =
and infrastructure), while some of it is marketing for the fund. They actua=
lly find that, for small funds, platforms =E2=80=9Cthat primarily focused o=
n pre-investment related activities =E2=80=94 marketing, community, investm=
ent operations =E2=80=94 outperformed the pooled average,=E2=80=9D while =
=E2=80=9Csmaller funds that focused primarily on post-investment activities=
 underperformed the pooled average.=E2=80=9D But for large funds, platforms=
 =E2=80=9Cprimarily focused on  post-investment related activities =E2=80=
=94 talent, business development/go-to-market, ESG=E2=80=9D outperformed.


  [3] An important variant is that the company does a big stock buyback, wh=
ich is a little bit like M&A: The activist makes money by optimizing the co=
mpany=E2=80=99s capital structure rather than its business.


  [4] Carl Icahn used to do that occasionally, but I figured that was more =
of a hobby than anything else.


