<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gorman, 65, is running Wall Street=E2=80=99s m=
ost closely watched horse race, vowing to have his successor in place in le=
ss than a year.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But what=E2=80=99s especially striking is Gorm=
an=E2=80=99s other declaration: He wants to defy deeply entrenched norms wi=
th a bloodless handoff =E2=80=94 in which the rejected finalists stay, avoi=
ding the usual cascade of shakeups and senior departures. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=C2=A0It=E2=80=99s a daring bet in an industry=
 where fragile egos and raw ambition make for messy handovers, sometimes de=
railing even the best-performing firms.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mike Mayo, the skeptic-in-chief among bank ana=
lysts, remains unconvinced.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe road is littered with CEO success=
ion that results in upheaval of those in the upper ranks,=E2=80=9D Mayo sai=
d. =E2=80=9CI just think it=E2=80=99s going to be a challenge to keep the t=
eam as cohesive as they currently are.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The three leading candidates =E2=80=94=C2=A0Te=
d Pick,=C2=A0Andy Saperstein=C2=A0and Dan Simkowitz =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9Care known to dine together frequently and even appear to enjoy each othe=
rs=E2=80=99 company,=E2=80=9D but of course that=E2=80=99s how they feel=C2=
=A0<em>now</em>. Now they are trying to win a competition in which they are=
, apparently, judged on how nicely they work with each other. Once two of t=
hem lose that competition they might feel different.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also this is good:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In one sign of the uncertainty, tw=
o senior colleagues privately bemoaned that they might not be close enough =
to whomever wins. They wouldn=E2=80=99t want to be hitched to the wrong can=
didate and lose clout.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I thought they were all best friends!</p>
