<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here are two broad theories of activist invest=
ing:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some companies have good opportunitie=
s but bad management, and an activist investor can buy some stock, harangue=
 the board and management to make changes, and improve the company=E2=80=99=
s business.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some companies could b=
e bought at a premium by other companies, and an activist investor can buy =
some stock, agitate for a sale, make the sale happen and collect the premiu=
m.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tra=
nsparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is, the job can be operational improvemen=
ts, or it can be sort of M&amp;A matchmaking. Intuitively =E2=80=9CM&amp;A =
matchmaking=E2=80=9D makes more sense: What are the odds that an activist h=
edge fund manager has better ideas for how to run a widget factory than the=
 widget company chief executive officer? The widget CEO specializes in widg=
ets, but the activist manager can specialize in making deals happen.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The operational-improvements model could, I su=
ppose, work through the cycle; there=E2=80=99s always some company somewher=
e that can be improved. The M&amp;A-matchmaker model does kind of depend on=
 the merger market though. Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/32361283.264411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2x=
lcy9pdHMtaGFyZC10by1iZS1hbi1hY3RpdmlzdC10aGVzZS1kYXlzLWdhZGZseS1pbnZlc3Rvcn=
MtdHJhaWwtc3RvY2stbWFya2V0LXJldHVybnMtMWYxZDg5ODU_bW9kPWhwX2xpc3RhX3BvczE/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcd030a50" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a Wall Street Journal story</a> =
about how activists are having a tough time in a tough merger market:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Activists generally seek out big returns by ac=
cumulating stakes in companies and then drumming up lots of noise in hopes =
of forcing boards to make changes or outright pushing businesses to sell. I=
n fact, they tend to favor the latter as it=E2=80=99s an almost surefire wa=
y to make a buck. But with fewer deals in the market, these firms have had =
one less arrow in their quivers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Predicting the stock market in 2023 has been t=
ough for many investors, said Bill Anderson, a senior managing director at =
Evercore and head of the firm=E2=80=99s global activism-defense business.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CBut this year=E2=80=99s downdraft in =
leveraged buyout activity has been really tough for activists,=E2=80=9D And=
erson said. =E2=80=9CThe deals they thought they would have to help their r=
eturns haven=E2=80=99t been out there.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, in a market where the biggest companies =
keep getting bigger, activism is harder because, what, you=E2=80=99re gonna=
 do activism at Apple?<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; b=
ackground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a></p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Plus, as Anderson pointed out, the=
 handful of tech companies that have played an outsize role in driving the =
stock market higher this year=E2=80=93like Apple, Alphabet, Meta Platforms,=
 Microsoft, Nvidia, Amazon.com and Tesla=E2=80=93are =E2=80=9Cnot really ac=
tivist targets.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The activist model is about taking smallish ba=
d companies and making them better, but the action these days is in huge go=
od companies getting better on their own.</p>
